message:
Hi. I'm curious what do you mean in ASP.NET Request Context. Is this also thread?
For example:


#================Code================
1 public class HomeController : Controller
2 {

    3 public async Task<string> Get()
    4 {
    5     var context = System.Web.HttpContext.Current; // here it has context
    6
    7     var jsonTask = await GetJsonAsync(new Uri("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos"));
    8     return jsonTask;
    9 }
    10
    11 public async Task<string> GetJsonAsync(Uri uri)
    12 {   
    13    using (var client = new HttpClient())
    14    {
    15      var jsonString = await client.GetStringAsync(uri).ConfigureAwait(false);
    16      var context = System.Web.HttpContext.Current; // here it is null
    17
    18      return jsonString;
    19    }
    20 }
21 }

From 3 to 15 lines it runs on ASP Request Context thread and after ConfigureAwailt(false) (from 15) it will run on new thread from thread pool. Am I right?
